an evaluation of autocode readability.wof the many requirements of an autocode, thepair of requirements "easy to read" and "easy to write" are not often compatible.  this paper arguesthat readability can be added automatically in the translation process so that the programmer canenjoy the utmost economy of expression, while for management a full and valid cobol version is printed to giveall the advantages of readability and compatibility.cacm march, ellis, p. v.ca jb march ,   : pm